Description:
A London GTUG Event

Javascript is the language of the web. But it's not always the right tool for the job. What if we could program the web safely and securely, in any language at all? Native Client makes that possible, by bringing together the safety of JavaScript with the flexibility of compiled code. As a bonus, there's usually a substantial performance improvement. This talk explains what Native Client is and how to use it to program web pages with C++.

title.value: Beyond JavaScript: Programming the web with Native Client
